gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: This polygon data layer represents hydrography for Manitowoc County, Wisconsin in 2016. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Manitowoc_HydroPoly_2016.gdb.[Lakes, ponds, and other open water features at least five acres in size. Features were delineated using Manitowoc County's 2010 digital orthophotograph.]

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [The lakes feature class was created primarily for cartographic use by Manitowoc County. They are not intended for legal or regulatory uses.]

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: [The data set is topologically structured polygon data with nodes at all intersections.]
[All open water features visible on the county's 2010 digital orthophotographs and at least 5 acres in size are included in this layer.]
[The relative horizontal positional accuracy for lake boundaries is +/- 6 feet based on the scale of the orthos, but may be much greater in areas with heavy vegetation.]
Attribute information remains the same as given by the author of the data.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: [Water feature linework was originally created by Aero-Metric, Inc. as part of a 2000 digital orthophotography project. They were updated by Ayres Associates as part of a 2005 digital orthophotography project and by the Manitowoc County GIS Office after a 2010 digital orthophotography project. The dataset was converted from an Esri shapefile to a file geodatabase in 2011.]
Exported original feature class into a new file geodatabase to maintain the original file format of the data and to conform to UW-Madison's data distribution plan.
Changed name of file from ‘LAKES_5ACRES’ to Manitowoc_HydroPoly_2016.
[Reference basemap to visually located water features.]

gmd:otherCitationDetails.gco:CharacterString: Color photography obtained during leaf off conditions and when there was no snow on the ground in the spring of 2010. They were used to produce orthophotography at a 12-inch ground pixel resolution. Control for the project was collected using Airborne Global Positioning System and ground-based GPS technology.

gmd:maintenanceNote.gco:CharacterString: Metadata was created as or translated to ISO 19139 for inclusion in the Big Ten Academic Alliance Geoportal.
